<BYLINE>
   By Agencies
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GTE, the US cellular telephone operator, has offered Dollars 22.50 a share
cash for the 10 per cent of Contel Cellular held by the public in a deal
worth Dollars 224m, agencies report.
GTE already owns the other 90 per cent.
Under the terms of the proposal, holders of about 10m Contel Class A common
shares would receive cash while the Class B shares owned by GTE would be
converted into shares of the merged entity.
After the merger, GTE's combined cellular businesses would be operated under
the GTE Mobilnet identity.
