FT  09 SEP 94 / Observer: Game boy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Delegates to the world population conference in Cairo have been quietly
amusing themselves by playing with a small pocket computer which can call up
population growth for all UN countries at the stab of a button. And, boasts
a delegate from the Vatican, the Holy See alone presents a perfect picture.
'Each time you push the button, the total remains at 1,000,' he explains.
