<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 94 / Observer: Phil me in
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
No doubt studying for an M Phil in the Evaluation of Public Services at
Middlesex's Brunel University is a fascinating exercise. There is certainly
a wealth of material on the doorstep.
A research company ringing to inquire about the contents of the course was
greeted by a voice on the switchboard professing ignorance of any such
discipline. The caller was put on hold for some minutes before the operator
returned. 'You still there? What course was it again?' A last-ditch attempt
was made to oblige. The caller was transferred to the university's
department of government - where an ancient answering machine cranked into
action.
</TEXT>
