FT  09 SEP 94 / Observer: Double dealing
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Barclays Stockbrokers is clearly mindful of Samuel Johnson's adage about
patriotism being the last refuge of the scoundrel. Unveiling its new
Barclayshare Overseas Service, it proudly announces that facilities for
dealing on the London Stock Exchange will be available to overseas nationals
as well as to 'expatriots'.
So what form of proof does Barclays require from potential customers that
they have abandoned their wicked ways?
