<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 94 / Plan to keep two-tier Cornwall
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Cornwall County Council should remain intact when local government is
reorganised, the Local Government Commission for England recommended
yesterday.
Its favourite option is to leave the two-tier system with a county council
and six districts. As alternatives, it suggests one all-purpose authority
for the county, or keeping the two-tier system but merging the districts
into three.
