<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 94 / Scottish survey figures amended
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The result of a survey which showed an alarming drop in the value of
electronic components which companies in Scotland obtain from local sources
has been amended following further analysis.
The original survey said the Scottish electronics industry obtained 5 per
cent of its material inputs from Scotland in 1994, compared with 12 per cent
in 1992, in spite of a 16 per cent rise in turnover to Pounds 9bn.
Yesterday the Scottish Partnership in Electronics for Effective
Distribution, which lobbies for better transport links, said the correct
figure for 1994 material inputs from Scotland should have been 10 per cent.
The value of Scottish-sourced inputs rose from Pounds 590m in 1992 to Pounds
660m in 1994.
