FT  09 SEP 94 / Disease reported on fish farm
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A suspected case of a fish disease equivalent to foot and mouth in cattle
has been reported on a fish farm, the Scottish Office said yesterday. Until
now the UK has been free of Viral Haemorrhagic Septicaemia, which does not
affect humans.
All fish movements from the area on the west coast Island of Gigha have been
banned.
