<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 94 / UN chief in Kashmir offer
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FARHAN BOKHARI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ISLAMABAD
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Boutros Boutros Ghali, United Nations secretary-general, yesterday
offered to play the role of 'honest broker' in an effort to resolve the
46-year Kashmir dispute, which continues to undermine relations between
India and Pakistan, writes Farhan Bokhari in Islamabad. The countries have
fought three wars, and thousands of soldiers still face each other in the
region.
'I have promised to be an honest broker to encourage a dialogue between the
two protagonists of this problem,' said Mr Boutros Ghali at the end of a
three-day visit to Pakistan, before leaving for New Delhi.
However, he conceded that his role would be limited without the agreement of
the two sides. In recent months western diplomats have been worried by
increased tensions along the disputed border.
