<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 94 / OECD endorses Swiss policies
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN RODGER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Swiss authorities have been given a fairly strong - if grudging -
endorsement from the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development
for their recent management of the Swiss economy. Switzerland is recovering
from three years of mild recession and the OECD, in its latest annual
assessment, forecasts 1.5 per cent real growth this year and 2.5 per cent
next year with low inflation. But it predicts that a further round of public
spending cuts and tax increases will be needed to eliminate a relatively
high budget deficit, and 'stepped up' efforts should be made to liberalise
many economic sectors and align standards with those of the EU.
