<HEADLINE>
FT  09 SEP 94 / World News in Brief: BR says it ran half its trains
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British Rail said it ran about half its passenger service during the latest
24-hour strike by signal workers, but strikers' leader Jimmy Knapp put the
proportion at one-third. A train and two cars were in near-collision at a
crossing in Long Eaton, Derbyshire, and a train was derailed at Bickley,
Kent. No one was hurt.
Picture, Page 9
