FT  08 SEP 94 / MPs petitioned on artillery ranges
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Farmers and villagers in Otterburn, Northumberland are to petition the
Commons for the removal of the Ministry of Defence's Otterburn Training Area
from designation as part of the Northumberland National Park.
The petitioners, who estimate the army's presence is worth Pounds 6m a year
to the local economy, are worried that recent criticism by environmentalists
of the presence of military training in the national park could jeopardise
the future of the artillery ranges, which date from 1911.
