<HEADLINE>
FT  08 SEP 94 / World Commodities Prices: Gold nears Dollars 390 mark -
Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The GOLD price found it impossible to break through the Dollars 390 a troy
ounce barrier on the London bullion market yesterday and the price ended at
Dollars 389.70, up Dollars 2.05. Dealers said Swiss buying started the
present rally and investment funds joined in yesterday on the New York
Commodity Exchange. But producer selling capped the market at about Dollars
390.
'At this level the price looks very attractive to the producers, especially
the Australians,' said one dealer. 'The New York guys seem to be interested
in buying gold on dips to around Dollars 387.50, so it's pretty well
supported,' he added.
ALUMINIUM was lively in after-hours trading in London. Speculative buying
helped run prices above stubborn technical resistance at Dollars 1,570 a
tonne. Last business was at Dollars 1,576.50, up Dollars 15.50, and traders
suggested a move towards Dollars 1,600 was likely.
Compiled from Reuters
