FT  08 SEP 94 / Observer: Clean fight
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Guess who is thumping the morality tub in the fight for a US senate seat in
Virginia? Why, none other than Oliver North, the retired marine lieutenant
colonel who lied to the US Congress over the Iran-Contra affair.
North - who says 'character always counts in a campaign' - accuses his main
rival in November's election, Senator Charles Robb, of having a 'seriously
flawed' character and lacking the 'moral force' to hold public office. The
attack is based on Robb's admission of 'socialising in situations not
appropriate for a married man', while serving the state as governor in the
mid-1980s.
