<HEADLINE>
FT  08 SEP 94 / Inquiry 'cleared Brent Walker'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN MASON, Law Courts Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
An investigation by Brent Walker in 1989 into press claims about irregular
transactions by its film division was thorough and proved there was nothing
improper, Mr George Walker, the company's former chairman, told an Old
Bailey jury yesterday.
Giving evidence in his defence Mr Walker said the allegations that two
transactions selling film rights worth more than Pounds 7m had not been
carried out at proper 'arms length' caused him considerable concern.
'It was very important to me because we were being accused of malpractice in
the company,' he said.
Mr Walker and Mr Wilfred Aquilina, a former Brent Walker finance director,
deny charges of theft, false accounting and conspiring to falsify the
company's accounts.
Mr Walker said the inquiry, by outside lawyers and accountants, proved the
transactions were 'totally right'.
The trial continues today.
</TEXT>
