<HEADLINE>
FT  08 SEP 94 / BT risks action on work patterns
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART, Labour Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
British Telecommunications and the National Communications Union could be
heading for industrial conflict over the company's proposals for new
attendance patterns.
BT wants more engineers available on weekday evenings and weekends and is
offering the 27,000 affected workers four separate attendance patterns. The
company says it expects employees to sign up to one of the patterns by
September 16.
Mr Tony Young, NCU general secretary, said yesterday that any attempt to
force employees to accept new contracts would lead to a strike ballot.
Union officials had hoped that their success in negotiating a Pounds 1,000
one-off payment for workers choosing the weekend patterns, and a clause
insisting that workers could volunteer for any of the new patterns, would be
sufficient to head off industrial action.
But a large majority of the employees has rejected the deal in a
consultative ballot.
</TEXT>
